From: Abhishek Vyas <abhishek.vyas@inventum.net>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmd_factory: keep operational certs across factory reset

The uCentral app factory reset (keep_redirector) preserves the birth
certs but not the operational cert/CA, leaving the AP without an
operational certificate. Add operational.pem and operational.ca to the
keep list; they are only archived when present (fs.stat guard).

Signed-off-by: abhishek vyas <abhishek.vyas@inventum.net>
---
--- a/command/cmd_factory.uc
+++ b/command/cmd_factory.uc
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@
 			"/etc/ucentral/cas.pem", "/etc/ucentral/cert.pem",
 			"/etc/ucentral/redirector.json", "/etc/ucentral/dev-id",
 			"/etc/ucentral/key.pem", "/etc/config/ucentral",
+			"/etc/ucentral/operational.pem", "/etc/ucentral/operational.ca",
 			"/etc/ucentral/profile.json"
 	];
 	for (let f in files)
